'''Liu Haidong''' (Chinese: 刘海东; [[Pinyin]]: ''Liú Hǎidōng''; born 28 February 1995) is a [[Chinese people|Chinese]] footballer.

==Club career==
Liu Haidong started his football career when he was promoted to [[Guangzhou Evergrande F.C.|Guangzhou Evergrande]]'s first team for the 2014 season. He made his debut for the club on 13 February 2014 against [[Guizhou Renhe F.C.|Guizhou Renhe]] in the [[2014 Chinese FA Super Cup]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Guizhou Renhe vs. Guangzhou Evergrande 1 - 0|url=https://int.soccerway.com/matches/2014/02/16/china-pr/super-cup/shanxi-baorong/guangzhou-yiyao/1640005/|work=Soccerway|accessdate=3 May 2014}}</ref> His league debut came on 3 May 2014 against [[Shanghai Shenxin F.C.|Shanghai Shenxin]] in a 1-0 away win. On 8 November 2014, he suffered a cruciate ligament rupture in the first training section after [[Fabio Cannavaro]] became the new manager of the club.<ref>{{cite web|title=恒大球员感叹卡帅真帅 1月5日吹响2015集结号|url=http://sports.qq.com/a/20141110/006750.htm|work=Tencent|accessdate=11 April 2016}}</ref> He recovered from injury and was included in Guangzhou Evergrande's reserve squad in the summer of 2016.
In March 2017, Liu loaned to [[China League Two]] side [[Heilongjiang Lava Spring]].<ref>[http://sjdb.hljnews.cn/news/40698.html 八名新援加盟黑龙江火山鸣泉队] at hljnews.cn 2017-03-13 Retrieved 2017-03-14</ref>
In March 2018, Liu loaned to [[China League Two]] side [[Hainan Boying]].<ref>[https://www.dongqiudi.com/archive/568489.html 官方：恒大旧将刘海东加盟海南] at dongqiudi.com 2018-03-09 Retrieved 2018-03-20</ref>

